<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>15191</anchor> <rss>jms-0081.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Course</taxon> <addr>jms-0081</addr>  <route>jms-0081.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year>  </date> <authors><author><link href="marcelofiore.xml" type="local">Marcelo Fiore</link></author><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Discrete Mathematics (2023–24)</title> <meta name="external">https://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/teaching/2324/DiscMath/</meta><meta name="venue"><link href="ucam.xml" type="local" title="University of Cambridge">University of Cambridge</link></meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The course aims to introduce the mathematics of discrete structures, showing it as an essential tool for computer science that can be clever and beautiful.</p><p>Michaelmas term lectured by <link href="marcelofiore.xml" type="local" title="Marcelo Fiore">Marcelo Fiore</link>; Lent term lectured by <link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</link>.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>15192</anchor> <rss>jms-007Z.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>jms-007Z</addr>  <route>jms-007Z.xml</route>  <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> <contributor><link href="alejandroaguirre.xml" type="local">Alejandro Aguirre</link></contributor><contributor><link href="larsbirkedal.xml" type="local">Lars Birkedal</link></contributor><contributor><link href="marcelofiore.xml" type="local">Marcelo Fiore</link></contributor></authors> <title>Courses taught by <link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>15193</anchor> <rss>jms-0080.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Course</taxon> <addr>jms-0080</addr>  <route>jms-0080.xml</route> <date><year>2022</year>  </date> <authors><author><link href="alejandroaguirre.xml" type="local">Alejandro Aguirre</link></author><author><link href="larsbirkedal.xml" type="local">Lars Birkedal</link></author><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Category Theory (Fall 2022)</title> <meta name="venue"><link href="jms-00GC.xml" type="local" title="Aarhus University">Aarhus University</link></meta><meta name="external">https://jonsterling.github.io/courses/ct-fall-2022/</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter/> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>15194</anchor> <rss>jonmsterling.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Person</taxon> <addr>jonmsterling</addr>  <route>jonmsterling.xml</route>   <title>Jon Sterling</title> <meta name="external">https://www.jonmsterling.com/</meta><meta name="institution"><link href="camcl.xml" type="local" title="Computer Laboratory">Computer Laboratory</link></meta><meta name="orcid">0000-0002-0585-5564</meta><meta name="position">Associate Professor</meta><meta name="phd-advisor">robertharper</meta><meta name="postdoc-advisor">larsbirkedal</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Associate Professor in Logical Foundations and Formal Methods at University of Cambridge. Formerly a <link href="jms-0061.xml" type="local" title="TypeSynth: synthetic methods in program verification">Marie Skłodowska-Curie Postdoctoral Fellow</link> hosted at <link href="jms-00GC.xml" type="local" title="Aarhus University">Aarhus University</link> by <link href="larsbirkedal.xml" type="local" title="Lars Birkedal">Lars Birkedal</link>, and before this a PhD student of <link href="robertharper.xml" type="local" title="Robert Harper">Robert Harper</link>.</p>
  
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
    
  
    
    
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>15195</anchor> <rss>marcelofiore.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Person</taxon> <addr>marcelofiore</addr>  <route>marcelofiore.xml</route>   <title>Marcelo Fiore</title> <meta name="position">Professor</meta><meta name="institution"><link href="camcl.xml" type="local" title="Computer Laboratory">Computer Laboratory</link>, <link href="jms-00GF.xml" type="local" title="Christ’s College">Christ’s College</link></meta><meta name="external">https://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/~mpf23/</meta><meta name="orcid">0000-0001-8558-3492</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><blockquote><strong>Interests:</strong> Mathematical models of computation; denotational and operational semantics of programming languages and interactive systems; type systems and program logics for functional and concurrent computation; applications of category theory to computer science.</blockquote></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>15196</anchor> <rss>ucam.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Institution</taxon> <addr>ucam</addr>  <route>ucam.xml</route>   <title>University of Cambridge</title> <meta name="external">https://www.cam.ac.uk/</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter/> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>15197</anchor> <rss>jms-008Q.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Meeting</taxon> <addr>jms-008Q</addr>  <route>jms-008Q.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>9</month> <day>11</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="2023-09-11" type="external">2023-09-11</link> / <link href="marcelofiore.xml" type="local" title="Marcelo Fiore">Marcelo Fiore</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>I discussed with <link href="marcelofiore.xml" type="local" title="Marcelo Fiore">Marcelo</link> the definition of single-variable substitution in the object classifier using the tininess of the interval. I plan to try and define this in Agda-flat; I am curious if I can get it to compute, using rewrite rules for the “amazing” transpose.</p><p>We also discussed the plan for the <link href="jms-0081.xml" type="local" title="Discrete Mathematics (2023–24)">Discrete Mathematics</link> course. My lectures should start somewhere in the set theory section, and then continue through regular languages and automata to the end.</p></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>